WEBVTT

00:03.003 --> 00:04.471
ANY RESEMBLANCE TO REAL ONES
IS PURELY COINCIDENTAL.

00:14.180 --> 00:15.849
-Hi.
-How are you?

00:16.616 --> 00:17.550
You were right.

00:19.052 --> 00:21.221
We've checked
all the surveillance cameras.

00:21.554 --> 00:23.023
And we've found it.

00:28.628 --> 00:30.830
-What's wrong?
-Nothing.

01:53.646 --> 01:58.551
THE FRAGILITY OF BODIES

02:14.200 --> 02:15.768
Excuse me?

02:15.835 --> 02:18.271
I'm looking for someone
who lives in this house.

02:18.338 --> 02:19.806
That is inhabited.

02:19.873 --> 02:21.274
I got this address.

02:21.741 --> 02:22.909
It's always been inhabited.

02:23.977 --> 02:26.112
Do you know this boy?

02:28.915 --> 02:30.917
This is to thank me
for the favors?

02:31.451 --> 02:33.052
This is crazy.
How much was it?

02:33.553 --> 02:35.688
Enough to ask you
for another favor.

02:38.224 --> 02:41.327
I need you to find
the address for this phone.

02:41.394 --> 02:42.795
I think this is the house
where lives the boy...

02:42.862 --> 02:45.031
that Carranza hit,
Nahuel Suárez.

02:45.932 --> 02:47.400
Nahuel Suárez...

02:48.001 --> 02:49.302
The address
was not on the file?

02:49.636 --> 02:52.438
It was.
But it is fake.

02:52.839 --> 02:54.040
It's a vacant lot.

02:54.107 --> 02:55.808
Give me a couple of hours
to see what I can do.

03:03.616 --> 03:07.687
-Jonathan Cisneros.
-Who is he?

03:07.754 --> 03:09.055
Another boy.

03:09.122 --> 03:10.890
The only one, out of the seven,
who was uninjured.

03:11.891 --> 03:12.992
There is nothing on the file.

03:13.393 --> 03:15.328
Not even who drove the train.

03:15.695 --> 03:16.763
And you want to find him.

03:17.230 --> 03:18.965
-I want to try.
-I'll do my best.

03:19.299 --> 03:20.967
Anyway, if there is
nothing on the file...

03:21.034 --> 03:22.802
-The judge was Romanín.
-Really?

03:23.870 --> 03:26.706
Ask you father. They play golf
together every week.

03:26.773 --> 03:27.740
I know.

03:28.074 --> 03:29.275
But my father
does not ride a bike.

03:29.609 --> 03:31.511
And the helmet
can not be returned.

03:34.113 --> 03:36.583
Two to zero!

03:36.983 --> 03:39.719
Since I became a Chacarita fan,
it's lost all the matches.

03:39.786 --> 03:41.054
Soccer is like that.

03:41.120 --> 03:42.455
Sometimes you win,
sometimes you lose.

03:43.756 --> 03:45.425
What's wrong with you?

03:50.763 --> 03:52.031
I have to move out.

03:53.132 --> 03:55.268
I can't continue living
in that lousy boarding house.

03:56.569 --> 03:57.937
I need a decent place
to take my daughter.

03:58.004 --> 03:59.372
Where she can have her own room.

03:59.706 --> 04:01.975
-Move out then.
-It's not so easy.

04:03.843 --> 04:05.645
I can't even afford
a one-bedroom apartment.

04:06.012 --> 04:08.615
Two months in advance.
A property as a warranty.

04:08.948 --> 04:10.149
It all a fortune.

04:10.216 --> 04:13.052
I can give you
my property as a warranty.

04:13.586 --> 04:15.989
Thank you very much.
But I need money.

04:19.626 --> 04:22.528
I've made up my mind.
I'll become a Chicago fan.

04:22.895 --> 04:24.797
-You can't do that.
-Why not?

04:24.864 --> 04:26.266
Because your team is Chacarita.

04:26.332 --> 04:29.135
You can't change teams
because yours is doing badly.

04:29.535 --> 04:30.703
It's just like life.

04:30.770 --> 04:31.871
You were born Chinese,
you'll die that way.

04:32.205 --> 04:33.406
You were born a Chacarita fan,
you'll die that way.

04:34.140 --> 04:35.675
I can choose to have
another citizenship though.

04:36.009 --> 04:38.611
Shut up, please.

04:41.080 --> 04:42.215
Come in.

04:45.018 --> 04:47.654
I've come to say hi.
So you don't complain about me.

04:48.554 --> 04:51.924
You're planning
a dinner party for the 23rd.

04:53.159 --> 04:56.362
For the 23rd.?
Is that necessary, dad?

04:56.429 --> 05:00.300
No, but we agreed to do that
with your sisters.

05:02.168 --> 05:03.836
Why don't we celebrate
her birthday...

05:03.903 --> 05:05.338
instead of the day
of her death?

05:05.705 --> 05:07.440
We don't get together
to celebrate her death.

05:07.774 --> 05:09.542
It's to remember
your mother's death.

05:09.876 --> 05:11.477
If you don't want to come,
it's fine.

05:11.844 --> 05:13.012
You don't have to.

05:15.515 --> 05:18.384
If all agree, let's do it.

05:19.018 --> 05:21.487
It can be either at home
or at Leti's.

05:21.821 --> 05:23.089
We can also meet
at my apartment.

05:23.156 --> 05:25.024
It's not big
but we are not so many.

05:25.591 --> 05:28.394
All right, your apartment then.

05:28.828 --> 05:30.663
I'll bring the food.
You make some dessert.

05:30.730 --> 05:32.699
There is no need.
I'll take care of everything.

05:34.033 --> 05:36.069
To make potato knishes
is not rocket science.

05:37.437 --> 05:39.005
Where did you get
the money from?

05:39.539 --> 05:40.907
I can't tell you.

05:41.607 --> 05:43.042
I won't tell anybody.

05:44.243 --> 05:46.112
Bullshit!
You'll spill the beans.

05:48.815 --> 05:49.949
You stole it.

05:50.316 --> 05:52.185
I didn't.
I can earn more if I want to.

05:52.885 --> 05:54.754
I also want to earn money.

06:00.626 --> 06:02.095
I want to buy
new soccer boots.

06:02.428 --> 06:05.932
They cost 1,000 pesos.
Replicas.

06:06.966 --> 06:09.268
The original ones cost
about 2,500.

06:10.169 --> 06:11.537
How will you get that amount?

06:13.940 --> 06:15.641
You think you're so smart.

06:25.084 --> 06:25.985
Here he is.

06:26.753 --> 06:29.188
Actually, he is not in a coma,
but in a vegetative state.

06:29.522 --> 06:31.858
-What is the difference?
-Does it matter?

06:33.426 --> 06:34.794
I'm sorry.
Two buses have crashed.

06:35.194 --> 06:36.396
They are bringing
the casualties over here.

06:36.796 --> 06:38.331
This will be a chaos
in a few minutes.

06:38.731 --> 06:39.832
Don't worry.

06:40.233 --> 06:42.802
My sister told me
it was a train accident.

06:43.136 --> 06:44.504
How did you get
that information?

06:44.871 --> 06:46.739
I can't remember.
I think a relative told us.

06:47.106 --> 06:49.308
-Who?
-His father or his uncle.

06:49.709 --> 06:51.444
Only his mother has come lately.

06:53.446 --> 06:54.914
Here we go.

06:55.782 --> 06:57.250
-Thanks.
-You're welcome.

07:55.775 --> 07:57.810
I've got the address
you were looking for.

07:58.177 --> 07:59.412
It's a shantytown.

07:59.846 --> 08:01.614
Los Piletones, in Soldati.

08:06.419 --> 08:07.753
Send it over to me, please.

08:10.990 --> 08:12.992
Are you there?

08:22.034 --> 08:25.137
Block Four, House Nr. 39.
Los Piletones.

08:25.204 --> 08:28.274
What about the other boy,
Jonathan?

08:38.985 --> 08:41.187
-How are you doing?
-Fine.

08:43.422 --> 08:46.092
Can you show me a draft
of your story?

08:47.026 --> 08:48.728
Actually, there is no draft.

08:49.762 --> 08:51.264
Tell me about it then.

08:53.366 --> 08:54.967
Right now?

08:55.034 --> 08:58.337
Or we can meet later.

08:58.404 --> 09:01.274
We can tell me
over coffee or dinner.

09:01.340 --> 09:02.275
How do you like that?

09:04.810 --> 09:07.613
I'll work something out
and I'll let you know.

09:08.748 --> 09:11.651
-Fine, let me know.
-Sure.

09:21.160 --> 09:23.329
Are you on the train?
I need to talk to you urgently.

09:23.396 --> 09:24.463
Call me when you can.

09:26.499 --> 09:27.733
Damn!

09:36.542 --> 09:39.779
I'm sorry.
I made a mistake.

09:41.013 --> 09:42.281
I'm so dumb.

09:46.185 --> 09:48.821
Cutini's zoo used to be here.
Did you know that?

09:49.322 --> 09:50.723
It was a gold mine.

09:51.824 --> 09:52.992
Until a boy tried to feed
a bear.

09:53.392 --> 09:55.361
And it torn his arm off.

09:57.797 --> 09:59.498
Thirty years have passed.

10:01.500 --> 10:02.969
There are people who say
they still see...

10:03.035 --> 10:04.437
loose animals out there.

10:05.905 --> 10:09.875
Deers, guanacos...
Those damn animals.

10:10.810 --> 10:11.978
Did you also buy this land?

10:13.980 --> 10:16.082
Who is the driver in the video?

10:16.482 --> 10:17.783
Lucio Valrossa.

10:19.085 --> 10:20.953
And the girl?
She's very nice.

10:21.287 --> 10:22.922
Verónica Rosenthal.

10:22.989 --> 10:24.457
Rosenthal...

10:24.523 --> 10:26.225
A Jewish girl, a reporter.

10:26.592 --> 10:28.327
It rings a bell to me.

10:28.761 --> 10:30.763
Her father is a lawyer.

10:33.633 --> 10:36.335
-What do we do now?
-Nothing.

10:37.603 --> 10:40.406
-We must stay alert.
-Nothing?

10:41.273 --> 10:42.441
Nothing for the time being.

10:48.147 --> 10:51.350
What happened to the bear
who tore the boy's arm off?

10:51.417 --> 10:54.420
-He became a carpet.
-Of course.

10:57.056 --> 11:00.393
That shouldn't have happened.
Cutini was an idiot.

11:00.793 --> 11:03.562
If you give food to a bear
and he'll eat up your hand.

11:08.801 --> 11:14.073
Perfect.
Thanks a lot. Bye.

11:21.447 --> 11:22.481
Did you finally rent anything?

11:22.815 --> 11:25.518
No way! Real state agencies
ask for a fortune.

11:25.584 --> 11:28.521
And owners don't rent
to unregistered employees.

11:28.587 --> 11:29.822
Those problems are solved
with money.

11:30.156 --> 11:31.624
I don't have any.

11:31.957 --> 11:33.359
-You could have a lot.
-How?

11:33.759 --> 11:36.295
You have a good eye.
You know what I need.

11:37.296 --> 11:38.564
Peque is wonderful.

11:38.998 --> 11:40.266
What you gave me
for finding Peque...

11:40.332 --> 11:42.535
was not enough
to pay for the downpayment.

11:42.601 --> 11:44.570
Find me another one like Peque
and I'll help you out.

11:55.014 --> 11:56.282
How is your father?

11:57.583 --> 11:59.819
Do you really want
to talk about my father?

12:00.152 --> 12:02.054
I love him, I want to know
how he is doing.

12:03.055 --> 12:06.025
-Tell me.
-He is fine.

12:07.026 --> 12:09.295
He is coming home this week,
together with my sisters.

12:09.361 --> 12:10.863
What is the occasion?

12:11.397 --> 12:13.733
It's my mother's
death anniversary.

12:15.668 --> 12:19.638
-How long ago was it?
-Five years.

12:21.974 --> 12:25.277
-You must be careful.
-Why?

12:26.045 --> 12:29.482
He'll see the panel on the wall
and he'll get worried.

12:29.548 --> 12:31.217
He'll think you are obsessed.

12:32.017 --> 12:34.820
Well, you are.
Very much obsessed.

12:34.887 --> 12:37.189
How are you, Vero?
Where are you?

12:37.990 --> 12:40.659
It's Thursday night.
You must be at Paula's bar.

12:41.293 --> 12:43.095
I've got some information
for you.

12:43.162 --> 12:44.463
Tell me what you want
me to do about it.

12:52.872 --> 12:56.142
I learned something
about Jonathan, the survivor.

12:56.208 --> 12:57.810
I talked to Romanín.

12:58.844 --> 13:01.614
He gave me the name
of the train driver.

13:01.947 --> 13:04.316
Carlos Romero.
Here is a picture of him.

13:18.364 --> 13:19.698
What?

13:19.765 --> 13:20.599
I have a friend who works
at the Federal Shooting Range.

13:22.067 --> 13:24.470
-I phoned him about the gun.
-What gun?

13:24.904 --> 13:26.272
-Come on, Vero.
-Okay, I know.

13:26.605 --> 13:29.275
I felt uneasy about that.
I asked him about it.

13:30.209 --> 13:33.078
Do you know they keep records
of all the guns used there?

13:33.145 --> 13:35.648
Yes, I do.
So?

13:36.382 --> 13:37.750
So?

13:42.688 --> 13:43.756
What is this?

13:43.823 --> 13:46.992
A record.
With dates and times.

13:48.761 --> 13:50.162
Valrossa went there
several times.

13:50.229 --> 13:51.463
To practise shooting
with his gun.

13:55.835 --> 13:57.703
He told me he had never
gone practising.

13:57.770 --> 13:59.305
He didn't even remember
he had that gun.

13:59.638 --> 14:02.341
He must have poor memory.
He went there many times.

15:00.933 --> 15:03.936
Hey, Rafa!

15:11.443 --> 15:14.914
-How are you?
-Fine. And you?

15:14.980 --> 15:17.383
-Do you remember Pizza?
-Hi, Pizza.

15:17.716 --> 15:18.851
-How are you?
-Fine.

15:18.918 --> 15:21.086
Why didn't you come over
the other night?

15:21.153 --> 15:23.389
I told you I couldn't.

15:23.455 --> 15:25.424
Don't worry.
It's okay.

15:25.758 --> 15:27.226
Today's is Piazza's
sister's birthday.

15:27.293 --> 15:28.928
-Why don't you come?
-That'll be great.

15:28.994 --> 15:31.363
-I don't think I can go.
-Come on!

15:31.430 --> 15:35.534
Do you want us to beg you?
It's an invitation.

15:37.202 --> 15:39.872
-Okay, but just for a while.
-Great.

15:39.939 --> 15:42.174
Bring something to drink.
Wine or beer.

15:43.475 --> 15:45.411
If you don't drop by,
we'll go fetch you.

15:45.778 --> 15:47.279
All right, see you.

16:01.727 --> 16:02.828
How are you?

16:02.895 --> 16:05.164
I met with Sandra,
Carranza's wife.

16:05.230 --> 16:06.699
She told me
she never talked to you.

16:06.765 --> 16:08.300
You told me something else.

16:08.901 --> 16:10.569
I didn't want to bother her.
I thought it was a bad time.

16:10.636 --> 16:12.504
You should've told me that.

16:12.571 --> 16:14.606
You said she didn't want
to see me instead.

16:15.908 --> 16:18.177
I also learned you went
to the Federal Shooting Range.

16:18.243 --> 16:19.311
You practised there many times.

16:19.645 --> 16:22.047
With the gun you told me
you didn't remember having.

16:23.215 --> 16:24.984
Are you married?
Do you have children?

16:25.050 --> 16:26.118
Is that true?

16:26.185 --> 16:27.319
I'm married, I have children...

16:27.386 --> 16:28.320
and I went
to the Federal Shooting Range.

16:28.387 --> 16:29.822
What for?

16:29.888 --> 16:32.992
To take my mind off things.
You concentrate, aim and fire.

16:33.058 --> 16:34.493
It's a soothing activity.

16:34.560 --> 16:36.662
Fishing and yoga
are soothing activities.

16:36.729 --> 16:38.230
Not shooting bullets.

16:40.466 --> 16:42.001
Why did you lie to me?

16:43.235 --> 16:44.570
Because you are a reporter.

16:45.537 --> 16:46.839
I'm just getting to know you.

16:47.606 --> 16:48.874
Did you give him the gun?

16:49.274 --> 16:52.144
-You like repeating questions.
-Did you?

16:52.211 --> 16:53.479
I told you I didn't.

16:54.613 --> 16:56.882
There were seven accidents
involving children...

16:56.949 --> 16:58.083
in the last five years.

16:58.150 --> 17:00.786
Six of them died,
only one survived.

17:01.320 --> 17:03.188
The driver that day
was Carlos Romero.

17:04.123 --> 17:08.160
Do you know him?
Personally?

17:08.227 --> 17:09.395
I want to meet him.

17:09.461 --> 17:10.763
I want him to tell me
what happened.

17:10.829 --> 17:13.832
-You know what happened.
-Yes, but I want to know more.

17:15.401 --> 17:18.203
You don't seem to understand.
There are children involved.

17:18.270 --> 17:21.540
You have children, Lucio.
I can't believe you don't care.

17:23.609 --> 17:26.745
-What are you laughing at?
-You are so funny.

17:26.812 --> 17:28.947
-Why?
-What children?

17:30.115 --> 17:31.884
You only care about yourself.

17:34.453 --> 17:35.788
You are an asshole.

17:38.657 --> 17:40.192
My shift is about to start.

18:12.825 --> 18:13.725
Hello?

18:14.393 --> 18:15.461
How are you feeling?

18:16.795 --> 18:18.130
